President Trump held a meeting with leaders of the airline industry in the State Dining Room of the White House. He commended the industry for supporting over 10 million jobs and creating almost $1 trillion in economic activity. Trump expressed his desire to improve customer service and reduce delays in air travel. He also discussed the need to modernize the air traffic control system, calling it outdated and wasteful. The president asked for suggestions on how to make the airlines more successful and competitive globally. The CEOs of various airlines, including Delta, Southwest, and United, voiced their concerns and recommendations, including the need for tax and regulatory reform, as well as modernizing the air traffic control system. They also discussed the need to improve airport infrastructure. Overall, the meeting focused on ways to enhance the airline industry and create more jobs in the United States.